user_question: How can I capture the Milky Way with my DSLR camera?
final_answer: To capture the Milky Way with a DSLR camera, use a wide-angle lens, set the aperture to f/2.8 or lower, ISO to 1600-3200, and shutter speed to 20-30 seconds. Find a dark location away from city lights.
